      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on pedicle screw geometry. Stiffness QoI changes 3.1% from coarse to medium and 0.9% from medium to fine mesh. Fine mesh selected for all production runs. Richardson extrapolation applied; GCI < 2% for all primary QoIs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver convergence criteria documented and residuals confirmed below tolerance for all production runs.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson iteration with force residual tolerance 1e-4 N and displacement tolerance 1e-6 mm. All 11 simulation runs converged within 50 iterations per load step. No divergence events recorded. Automatic time-stepping with bisection enabled."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model setup reviewed by independent analyst; boundary conditions and loading confirmed against ASTM F1717 protocol.",
      "rationale": "Independent review of boundary condition application, load application point, and constraint definitions performed by second analyst. Checklist-based review against ASTM F1717 standard confirmed correct implementation of fixed-fixed boundary conditions and axial-bending load application."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Governing physics captured by model form appropriate for the COU loading regime and QoIs of interest.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear quasi-static FEA with bilinear isotropic hardening material model selected. Large-displacement formulation (NLGEOM on) applied to capture post-yield response. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) between screw and block interfaces. Model form appropriate for static compression-bending per ASTM F1717."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric inputs sourced from measurements or certified material data with documented uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V ELI material properties sourced from tensile coupon testing (n=5 coupons per lot). Geometric inputs from CMM measurements of production screws. Friction coefficient from literature (ASTM G115 pin-on-disk, titanium on UHMWPE). Input uncertainty characterised and propagated for stiffness and yield force QoIs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test samples representative of production geometry and material; sample size adequate for statistical comparison.",
      "rationale": "N=11 production pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. Screws drawn from same production lot as CMM-measured specimens used for model geometry. Dimensional inspection confirms all screws within drawing tolerances. Sample size supports mean and standard deviation estimation for all three QoIs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of COU conditions or a single well-characterised condition with documented rationale.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single load configuration (ASTM F1717 standard geometry, 10 mm offset). Only one test condition evaluated due to resource constraints; this factor is below required level. Rationale accepted by team given that ASTM F1717 prescribes a single standard configuration and clinical loading envelope is bounded by this configuration."
    },
